playerCharacter.name: pm
playerCharacter.backstory:
Pm was never a hero; he was a survivor. Born in the soot of a garrison town, he spent a decade as a nameless shield-bearer for the Iron Duchy. They called him "Pm"a grim shorthand for *post-meridiem*because he was always the last soul standing when the sun dipped low and the killing fields fell silent. He has watched kings fall and tyrants rise, learning that every "noble cause" eventually bleeds into the same grey mud. 

He doesnt fight for glory, nor does he strike out of malice. He fights because the rhythm of steel on steel is the only language he speaks fluently. When his regiment was sacrificed for a lords strategic whim, Pm simply walked away. He carried his dented plate and notched blade into the wild, seeking neither redemption nor ruin. In a world of fanatical gods and screaming monsters, Pm remains the steady, indifferent centera blade for hire, answering only to the weight of his own coin.
